  "prompt": "How many First Ladies have refused to live in the White House?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, there has been one First Lady of the United States who refused to live in the White House. In 1809, Thomas Jefferson's daughter, Martha Jefferson Randolph, served as the official hostess during her father's presidency, as Jefferson\u2019s wife had passed away years before he became president. Martha often stayed at her own home and did not live in the White House full-time. Another notable example is Melania Trump, who delayed her move to the White House until June 2017, citing her son's schooling as the reason.\n\nHowever, there is no record of any First Lady outright refusing to live in the White House for the entirety of the presidential term.",
